function pyramid = RRgaussianPyramid(im, numLevels)% pyramid = RRgaussianPyramid(im, numLevels)%% Computes a GaussianPyramid of image im, with numLevels levels.  % Does not include the highest frequency level (the original image).  % Returns a cell structure containing the levels of the pyramid.%% Reference: % Burt, P., & Adelson, E.H. The Laplacian Pyramid as a% Compact Image Code. IEEE Trans. on Communication,% COM-31:532-540, 1983.% code by Ruth Rosenholtz% The "gaussian" is a separable filter:% G = [0.05, 0.25, 0.40, 0.25, 0.05].pyramid = cell(numLevels, 1);pyramid{1} = im;for i=2:numLevels,    if i==2,        tmp = im;    else        tmp = pyramid{i-1};    end    pyramid{i} = reduce(tmp);       % This uses my old reduce program, which reflects the image about the    % border before filtering, to minimize edge effects.endreturn;